  "issue_title": "feature: build screen context from accessibility tree",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #38\n\n## Problem\n\nAfter defining the screen context model, TouchPilot needs a reliable builder that converts Android Accessibility observations into that model.\n\nRaw Accessibility trees are noisy and inconsistent. The builder should normalize data into a smaller, useful context for local reasoning and suggested actions.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nImplement an Accessibility-to-screen-context builder:\n\n```text\nAccessibility observation\n  -> normalize nodes\n  -> extract visible text\n  -> extract clickable targets\n  -> extract input fields\n  -> extract bounds/state\n  -> produce ScreenContext\n```\n\nThe builder should keep raw observation details available for debugging, but the reasoning core should use the normalized context.\n\n## User workflow\n\nWhen the user asks `What can you do here?`, TouchPilot should first build screen context from the active Android screen and then generate a local summary or suggestions from that context.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis is the primary screen-understanding path. It avoids requiring screenshot vision models for normal Android screens.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\n- Builder output should remain compatible with log redaction.\n- Sensitive fields such as passwords, tokens, messages, and account data should be marked or redacted where possible.\n- The builder should not create executable actions directly; it should only produce context.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Build screen context from current Accessibility observation data.\n- [ ] Extract visible text nodes.\n- [ ] Extract clickable targets with bounds and stable identifiers when available.\n- [ ] Extract input fields and basic state.\n- [ ] Extract scrollable state where available.\n- [ ] Keep raw observation and normalized context separate.\n- [ ] Add tests with fake/sample Accessibility data.\n- [ ] Existing observe/tool behavior remains compatible.\n\n## References\n\n- Parent issue: #38\n- Depends on: screen context model issue\n- `docs/TOOL_SPEC.md`\n- `docs/LIVE_TESTING.md`\n",
